properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 27 at 2:01PM PST until January 28 at 5:00AM PST by NWS Spokane WA
properties.description:
...SNOW DEVELOPING THIS EVENING AND OVERNIGHT...

* WHAT...Snow expected for the higher elevations around
Wenatchee and Chelan as well as portions of the Waterville
Plateau. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches with
locally up to 6 inches west of Highway 97.

* WHERE...Number 2 Canyon, Waterville, Withrow and Badger
Mountain Road.

* WHEN...From 4 PM this afternoon to 5 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The heaviest snow is expected to fall
during the evening hours.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM PST TUESDAY FOR THE HIGHER ELEVATIONS AROUND WENATCHEE AND CHELAN
